We believe that all motorists should not be the last to to find out problems regarding their vehicles. We also strongly believe that all motorists would like to be informed of these issues and that is exactly what this platform is aimed at doing; allowing drivers to alert each other as they will wish to be alerted. In order to protect the experience and safety of the drivers who use Local Buzzard, there are some limitations on the type of content and behaviour that we allow.

All individuals accessing or using Local Buzzard services must adhere to the policies set forth in the Rules. Failure to do so may result in Local Buzzard taking one or more of the following enforcement actions:

* requiring you to send an apology to the individual whom you have caused harm to;

* temporarily limiting your ability to create send or receive alerts to and from Local Buzzard users;

* asking you to verify your account/driving licence via a three-way telephone call to DVLA;

* permanently suspending your account(s).

If you attempt to evade a permanent suspension by creating new accounts, we will suspend your new accounts.
Please note that we may need to change these Rules from time to time and reserve the right to do so. This is the most current version as of December 2018.

Local Buzzard may ask users to provide proof that their registered vehicle belongs to them. This could be done via asking the user to scan and email the following documents:
* V5c Certificate;
* Vehicle Insurance Documents;
* Any other Document deemed appropriate at the time.
